The paper deals with the performance analysis of the Generalized LASSO algorithm for recovering structured signals from compressed noisy measurements. This falls under the category of signal processing (cs.SP) and machine learning (cs.LG). The analysis heavily relies on the use of Gaussian min-max theorem (GMT), which is a tool from information theory (cs.IT). The paper also derives an asymptotic lower bound on the minimum conic singular values of isotropically random orthogonal (i.r.o.) matrices, which is a problem in numerical analysis (cs.NA). Finally, the paper deals with the performance comparison of different ensembles of measurement matrices, which is a topic in statistical inference (cs.SI).
